items.name: Positive-Integers-Porperties
items.description: A small Java math library containing useful methods for computing positive integers properties.

items.name: ViewBuilder
items.description: ViewBuilder for Android is a library for easily building useful views like Tags, Spinner, AutoCompleteTextView, ...

items.name: FilterMenuBar
items.description: A simple but useful menu bar for filtering and many other scenarios.

items.name: Stuffed
items.description: A framework useful for evaluating static and streaming classifiers, on large and unlabelled datasets.

items.name: golympian
items.description: Useful library for android development generally. Simplify your project with this multi functional library

items.name: TextManipulator
items.description: A program which allows the user to "manipulate" text using useful functions

items.name: Samantha
items.description: Samantha is a smart assistant, she extracts useful information from your sms and mails, and automatically make notifications for you.

items.name: TotemEssentials
items.description: A Minecraft 1.12 mod that adds a new totem crafting system to create many useful totems.

items.name: dftools
items.description: The DFTools project offers features useful for dataflow modeling tools such as the Open RVC-CAL Compiler (Orcc) and PREESM.

items.name: common-libraries
items.description: The Common Libraries is a collection of useful libraries that are used by the Consent2Share (C2S) APIs.

items.name: plugin-based-system
items.description: This is a simple example of a plugin based system. Simple and easy to learn and very useful when we want to have a scalable system.

items.name: pkg-config-support-for-eclipse-cdt
items.description: Provides automation of configuration needed for projects using pkg-config, such as GTK+ and gtkmm. Very useful time-saving tool for all C, C++ programmers using Eclipse.

items.name: FastInv
items.description: FastInv is a complete Bukkit API allowing you to easily create menus with clickable items all in one class and with useful features

items.name: Ohm
items.description: Ohm is a java library for FRC robots. It is intended to augment the features of WPILib with tools that we found useful in our programs.

items.name: JModule
items.description: Java CLI development library that lets you organize commands by functionality. Supports tab completion, history toggling, chained commands, and other useful features

items.name: moar-concurrent
items.description: This module contains a collection of useful builders and concurrency classes to assist in modeling complex or overly tweakable concurrent processing pipelines.

items.name: spring-utils
items.description: The repository where all the useful classes of the last project are put to use them with more fun for the next project.

items.name: Java-Distributed-Hash-Cracker
items.description: Written for CIS 4278, Computer Security in 2008 as part of my undergraduate studies. I keep it around because it was useful for learning the OpenChord DHT library

items.name: AndroidMobileNumberVerification
items.description: A sample android app that validates user entered mobile number based identity. It sends an SMS to the number entered by the user, and intercepts the SMS to verify it. If the user enters a wrong mobile number, the verification fails. Useful for mobile apps and games that want to use phone numer as bunique id.

items.name: GuiceJumper
items.description: The Smokejumper supplemental classes for Guice. These are utility classes and useful modules which do not depend on anything more than the most recent version of Guice and its dependencies.

items.name: TokenJar
items.description: Burp Suite extension. Useful for managing tokens like anti-CSRF, CSurf, Session values. Can be used to set params that require random numbers or params that are computed based on application response.

items.name: RMD-Calculator
items.description: Android app that calculates the Required Minimum Distribution (aka. Minimum Required Distribution or RMD) values for people between the ages 70-115+. No personal information is stored on an external server. This is most useful for US residents.

items.name: acpi_call_GUI
items.description: This is a java program that allows the user to simply install and use acpi_call kernel module via graphic Interface, and also provides an useful script that automatically recompiles the kernel after each update.

items.name: jar-enumerator
items.description: Command line utility that extracts the methods of classes in a JAR file. Filtering by a variety of class types and modifiers is supported. Useful if you ever need to know what is in a JAR - especially when you want to explore a public API and don't have the Javadocs.

items.name: ProjectGoldStarsX
items.description: Project GoldStars X is a full-screen Java program designed to appear as a virtual operating system. It includes many features, such as a calculator, a notes application, a personal assistant, and more! It can serve as a useful productivity tool, as well as a a project to help people trying to learn and/or experiment with Java.

items.name: BuildCraft-Addon_Basic-Machines
items.description: This mod adds a few machines to make BuildCraft more useful to the early-game in Minecraft. These machines include a BuildCraft-powered furnace, low capacity battery buffer, and powered mining tools.. (developed under the Minecraft Mod Public License: http://www.mod-buildcraft.com/MMPL-1.0.txt)

items.name: strangemachines
items.description: Strange Machines is a Java library for working with state machines. State machines can be useful when working with asynchronous events, parsing or games. The purpose of the state machine in this library is to enable a definition which states and transitions are valid and then make sure that a program that uses the state machine follows these rules.

items.name: tools4j-validator
items.description: Validation Framework. Useful for Java Swing applications or any kind of data validation with special prerequisites. Easy to perform validation of the popular Java data types without Java Beans concept. Constraints storable in JSON format. Dynamic validation and simple business rules approach.

items.name: ImageCompare
items.description: This program detects duplicate images in a directory and it's subdirectories. The user supplies the URL of a directory on their computer, and the program searches all the files in the directory (and it's sub directories) for any images that are duplicates. Useful for when dealing with a hard drive backup that creates duplicate images.

items.name: yoursway-ide
items.description: An unfinished project to implement a TextMate-style IDE in Java/SWT. Feel free to reuse under the MIT license. I don't think it compiles and runs, but parts and components may prove to be useful. (A legacy of a closed-down company I have owned.)
